frus:attachment.p:
thence the course of this river downstream, thence the Tisza
                                downstream to a point to be fixed on it below Badalo and near this
                                village;

a line to be fixed on the ground leaving in Ruthenian territory
                                Badalo, Csoma, Macsola, Asztely and Deda, and in Hungarian territory
                                Bereg-Surany and Darocz;

a line to be fixed on the ground leaving to Czecho-Slovakia the
                                villages of Miglecznemeti and Pereny and to Hungary the village of
                                Tornyosnemeti;

the watershed between the Bodva on the north and the Rakacza on the
                                south, leaving in Hungarian territory, however, the road on the
                                crest south-east of Buzita;

a line to be fixed on the ground leaving to Czecho-Slovakia Janok,
                                Tornahorvati and Bodvavedegi; and to Hungary, Tornaszenuakab and
                                Hidvegardo;

a line to be fixed in the ground following approximately the
                                watershed of the Rima to the north and the Hangony and Tarna rivers
                                to the south;

a line to be fixed in the ground leaving to Hungary the villages and
                                mines of Salgo and Zagyva-Rona, and passing immediately south of
                                Somos-Ujfalu station;
